external_knowledge:
- "Shining stars" refers to active players;
- "Team emblems" and "full team names" refer to the `team_abbreviation` and `team_name` columns, respectively;
- "Total points" and "games played" refer to the `total_points` and `total_games` columns, respectively;
- "Contract values" refer to the `total_contract_value` column;
- "Average points per game" is calculated as `total_points / total_games` and rounded to two decimal places.

- "First round" refers to the top 30 draft picks in the draft;
- "Played for multiple teams" means the player has been part of more than one team during their career;
- "Currently active" means the player is still playing in the league.

sql:
SELECT AVG(contract_value) 
FROM player_team_history 
WHERE start_year = 2015;

WITH LeagueAverage AS (
    SELECT AVG(points) AS avg_points FROM performance_stats
)
SELECT MAX(points) AS highest_points
FROM performance_stats
WHERE points > (SELECT avg_points FROM LeagueAverage);

external_knowledge:
- "Stellar performers" refers to players with the highest average points scored per game;
- "Top-ranked stars" refers to players ranked highest in the `PlayerRankings` CTE;
- "Boast" implies that the teams have these high-ranking players;
- The query ranks players within their teams, not across the entire league.

- "stands tallest" refers to the team with the highest rank based on total points and wins;
- "crowned with the most points and victories" refers to the team with the highest total points and total wins;
- "shining brighter than the rest" refers to the team that ranks first in the league.

- "shining stars" refers to players who have performed exceptionally well;
- "remained active" indicates that the players are currently active in the league;
- "shone brightly in the most recent season" means the players had the highest rank (most recent year) in the performance statistics;
- "scoring more than 500 points and pulling down over 200 rebounds" refers to the conditions `p.total_points > 500 AND p.total_rebounds > 200`;
- "teams do these stars currently call home" means the most recent team the player was associated with, determined by the `end_year` in the `player_team_history` table.

- "Donned more than one team's jersey" refers to players who have played for more than one team;
- "The grand stage of the league" refers to the professional sports league where the players compete;
- "Represented" refers to the team the player was part of during the season.

- "stars shining brightly" refers to players scoring high points;
- "100-point mark" is the threshold for the average points scored;
- "brilliance of these stars" refers to the average points scored by players.
